Beech Ban Protects Sand Lizard                        Page   1 of   4                                        BELLAMY PRAISES BEACH BAN TO PROTECT   LIVELY LIZARD                                                                 By a CORRESPONDENT, THE GUARDIAN       October 28 1985                                                              Holidaymakers have been barred from a  busy beach to protect the rare sand    lizard.                                                                       The agreement on a temporary ban by    councillors at Ainsdale, near          Southport, was welcomed by the         conservationist Dr David Bellamy as a  'super decision', Sefton council's     tourism committee voted to ban the     public from a section of the beach for a trial period of 12 months beginning  in March.                                                                     It is another victory for              